<br />
........4. <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=19235" target="_blank" class="postlink">Blackand Berserker's Axe</a>
<br />
........5. <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=19271" target="_blank" class="postlink">Cermonial Hate Candle</a>
<br />
<a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=11660" target="_blank" class="postlink">Crew Chief Hanriesaf</a> (about 10000hp, max hits around 150)
<br />
.....<span style="font-style: italic">Loot:</span>
<br />
........1. Weapons 5pp to vendor
<br />
........2. Various low end gems between 9pp and 47pp to vendors
<br />
........3. Various research pages and runes
<br />
........4. <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=19184" target="_blank" class="postlink">Brined Shoulderpads</a>
<br />
........5. <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=19156" target="_blank" class="postlink">Zraxthril Splinted Cloak</a>
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Breaking the camp:</span>
<br />
1. pull the wandering Blackhand Guardian that roams across the bridge.
<br />
2. run South along the lava river and pull the mob behind the rock. This is usually a Soot Covered Miner or an Exhausted Miner. If by chance this is the Exhausted Bloodtusk be ready for a fight. Have your pet heals ready as he will tear through the pet and usually takes at most 1/2 my mana.
<br />
3. Along the South wall there will be a doorway to the Furious/Vehement room with 2 mobs in the doorway. Pull the mob on the right out of the doorway and back towards the lava river.
<br />
4. Pull the mob on the left of the doorway out of the doorway and back towards the lava river.
<br />
5. Hugging the West (right) wall of the doorway you should be able to target the mob guarding the other side of the doorway. Pull the mob out the doorway and back towards the lava river.
<br />
6. Hugging the East (Left) wall of the doorway you should be able to target the mob guarding the other side of the doorway. Pull the mob out of the doorway and back towards the lava river.
<br />
7. Walk through the doorway slowly while looking to the West (Right). There should be a target in the corner. Start casting Malisement and send pet right away. You will want to fight him in that corner and should not get aggro from any other mobs in the room.
<br />
8. Pull the mob just to the south (right in front of you) and kill it in the corner.
<br />
9. Slowly move towards the center of the room (Whle not aggroing the mob in the middle of the room). There will be a mob in the second groove along the West wall. Pull the mob back to the corner.
<br />
10. Pull the mob in the middle of the room to the West wall of the room.
<br />
11. Pull the mob guarding the right side of the South exit back towards the West corner.
<br />
12. Pull the mob guarding the left side of the South exit back towards the West corner.
<br />
13. Pull the mob in the South East corner back towards the West wall of the room.
<br />
14. The last two mobs in the North East corner are kinda close together. From the West side of the room send the pet in and sit down. Once the pet hits the mob the mob will charge you (Sitting Aggro). Back off the pet to get the mob away from the other one and towards the middle of the room.
<br />
15. Pull the final mob in the North East corner back towards the middle of the room.
<br />
16. In the North East groove there is a pile of bones. Just sit there and med while facing the North exit. Mobs will begin to spawn and just work your way around the room again.
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Special Notes:</span>
<br />
1. Always keep damage shield up on the pet.
<br />
2. There is no need to heal the pet if you let it med after each fight for a short while. 
<br />
3. You will usually get around the room before burnout wears off and it will take about 3 casts of damage shied ( about 4 mobs per a damage shield).
<br />
4. The first 2 mobs in the cycle (outside the room) are only killed to break the camp. Unless you have the mana I would not suggest adding them in the cycle.
<br />
5. Sometimes when killing the Furious Blackhands and Vehement Blackhands, Crew Chief Hanriesaf will spawn on their death. Always be ready for this.
<br />
6. Mobs do not walk when low on hitpoints.
<br />
7. The first round of the cycle is the most mana intensive due to the extra mobs you fought to break into the room.
<br />
8. Alter the tactics that would best accomodate your play style. If you are conjuration based Mage healing and conjuration based nukes may be more mana efficient than 2 nukes with Firebolt of Tallon. 
<br />
9. It is a good idea to ensure Malisement lands before nuking. These mobs have decent resists and the mana loss on a resisted nuke can really hurt.
<br />

<br />
If this walkthrough helps and when time permits I will post other LoY camps for the solo Mage.
<br />

<br />
Kirobei</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
